    <text id="A9512T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jackson asks for McFarland's continued prayers and support.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>To 
                    <name type="recipient">Rev. Dr. McFarland </name>
                    <name type="place">Clarke County, Va.</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1862-10-30">Oct. 30th, 1862</date>
                        <name type="place">Clarke County, Va.</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My dear Doctor,</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your kind and christian letter of the 16th <abbr expan="instant">inst.</abbr>
                    with the accompanying resolutions have been received. I write this note to thank
                    you for having so effectually complied with my request, and to ask that your
                    prayers and christian efforts be continued as before requested. My trust is in
                    God, and it is a great comfort to me to know that He answers prayer. I am very
                    thankful to our kind Heavenly Father for restoring you to health. I hope that
                    both your sons, if not entirely well at present soon will be.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Your much attached friend,</salute>
                    <signed>T.J. Jackson</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
